Row Header Column is a Column always present at the start of the grid where each cell of this column will work as a row header.
The following example demonstrates the grid with a Row Header Column with no additional configuration.

To enable the Row Header Column, set the column property `enableRowHeaderColumn=true` in the Grid Options .

```{% frameworkTransform=true %}
const gridOptions = {
    enableRowHeaderColumn: true
}
```

{% gridExampleRunner title="Row Header Column" name="row-header-column-default" /%}

## Cell Selection

When the grid is configured with [Cell Selection](./cell-selection/), the Row Header Column will automatically integrate with it. This integration works
by selection of cells of the row when a cell in the Row Header Column is clicked. To prevent this, the `suppressCellSelectionIntegration` option can be used.

```{% frameworkTransform=true %}
const gridOptions = {
    enableRowHeaderColumn: true,
    cellSelection: true
}
```

